From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Fri, 2 May 2026 13:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 3/4] Add package.json to PULSE for dependency resolution

Pulse daemon imports six external npm packages (smol-toml, grammy,
@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk, minisearch, jose, yaml) but ships
without a package.json. On NixOS the wrapper runs `bun install` in
the PULSE directory during installation; without a manifest bun
cannot resolve the dependencies and Pulse crashes on start.

---
 Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PULSE/package.json | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PULSE/package.json

diff --git a/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PULSE/package.json b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PULSE/package.json
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..0000001
--- /dev/null
+++ b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PULSE/package.json
@@ -0,0 +1,14 @@
+{
+  "name": "pai-pulse",
+  "version": "5.0.0",
+  "private": true,
+  "description": "PAI Pulse daemon dependencies",
+  "dependencies": {
+    "smol-toml": "*",
+    "grammy": "*",
+    "@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk": "*",
+    "minisearch": "*",
+    "jose": "*",
+    "yaml": "*"
+  }
+}
--
2.53.0

